content:
Create a custom messaging component so agents can embed an external mobile app in enhanced Apple Messages for Business messaging sessions. Customers can then access the appâ€™s capabilities, such as search functionality, within their Apple Messages chat.

This article applies to Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, enhanced WhatsApp, enhanced Facebook Messenger, enhanced SMS, and enhanced Apple Messages for Business channels.

To create messaging components: Customize Application AND View Setup and Configuration or System Administrator. To send and receive messages in Messaging: Messaging Agent.

You can also use custom messaging components to share custom Lightning Web Components, custom iMessage extensions, or any URL that opens in a web view.

Step 1: Create a Custom Messaging Component

* From Setup, enter Messaging Components in the Quick Find box, and then select Messaging Components.
* Click New Component, and then click Next.
* Enter a prompt and upload an image to show with the prompt.
* Enter a name and description for your component.
* Assign an informative name so agents know when to use the component.

Step 2: Send a Custom Messaging Component in a Messaging Session

* During an active messaging session, click the messaging component action in the messaging window.
* Select the component that you want to share and click Insert.
* Click Send.
title: Custom Messaging Components in Salesforce Service Cloud
